  "texts": [
    "Drafting: starts with an empty graph and progressively adds undirected edges between pairs of nodes with the highest MI scores, if there is not currently an undirected path between the pair.",
    "This creates a maximum spanning tree.",
    "That is, where there is one, and only one, path between every pair of variables and the sum of edge scores is a maximum.",
    "This tree is used as a good starting point for the next phase. 2.",
    "Thickening: adds edges between non-adjacent nodes if there is no Sepset in the set of shared neighbours between the two nodes, as described above. 3."
  ],
